00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:48,650
Yes. The side.

278
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,080
OK.

279
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,520
Why doesn't your father open a shop with Mrs. Zou?

280
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:06,870
Why should he?

281
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,410
That place is a hit.

282
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,920
They don't have to pay shop rent or taxes there,

283
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:15,810
and it also have government's support.

284
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,480
It's a pure money-making deal.

285
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:20,260
Mrs. Zou can't handle it all alone,

286
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,620
so if your dad helps out,

287
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:25,530
it's like their own shop.

288
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:28,760
Isn't that way better than just earning those trivial salaries?

289
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,590
That's not gonna happen.

290
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:36,920
My father, he won't be willing to do that.

291
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:37,900
Why not?

292
00:15:39,610 --> 00:15:40,400
Come here.

293
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,490
What? Mrs. Zou is not...

294
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:48,730
a widow?

295
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:54,760
Mrs. Zou has a husband.

296
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:56,630
He is working outside.

297
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,240
You mean,

298
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:04,220
they are afraid of the gossips?

299
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,700
I always feel like she's lying to my dad.

300
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,330
I guess she has divorced her husband.

301
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:15,920
You see,

302
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:17,950
she has lived here for so many years.

303
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,480
But her husband never came back during the holidays.

304
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:22,470
Is that normal?

305
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:26,760
Are you listening?

306
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:27,690
I heard that.

307
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:29,500
You mean Mrs. Zou is not a widow?

308
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:33,300
Yes. But my father always denies that.

309
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:34,970
I guess,

310
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,060
your dad knows it very well.

311
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:44,070
Your dad is so close to some other woman.

312
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,310
Don't you feel a bit of uncomfortable?

313
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,400
No.

314
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,560
I once persuaded my father to marry her.

315
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:52,910
From what I can remember,

316
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,410
he's been a single dad all along.

317
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,270
I can't let him live like this forever, right?

318
00:16:58,600 --> 00:16:59,590
Have you ever considered to

319
00:16:59,610 --> 00:17:00,960
let your dad remarry your mom?

320
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:01,640
Never.

321
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,410
I prefer Mrs. Zou.

322
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:07,910
I don't want to see my father suffer again.

323
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:11,750
In fact, my father

324
00:17:11,829 --> 00:17:13,359
not joining Mrs. Zou to open the store

325
00:17:14,079 --> 00:17:16,160
isn't just because he's worried about what people might say.

326
00:17:17,589 --> 00:17:20,230
You see, this shop belongs to Mrs. Zou

327
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:23,900
my father definitely feels embarrassed to get involved in it.

328
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:27,579
We are both men.

329
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:28,880
We can relate to that.

330
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,830
If it were any other woman

331
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:33,210
there might be a chance,

332
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:37,680
but with Mrs. Zou, it's impossible.

333
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:44,180
Right.

334
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:48,420
Be carful, man.

335
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:50,450
Mr. Bai,

336
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:52,320
the factory manager has something to tell you. Go to his office now.

337
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,000
Hurry up.

338
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:53,830
OK. OK.

339
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:07,670
Sir.

340
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,860
-Bai, you're here. Come here. Have a seat. -OK.

341
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:14,670
-Have some tea. -OK. Thank you.

342
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:18,800
Bai, our factory decides to fire you.

343
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:25,360
Sit down. Sit down.

344
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:30,760
Director, you know my situation.

345
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:32,890
My son just started high school,

346
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:35,180
we need money to support his study.

347
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:37,190
I also have to look after the elder in my family.

348
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:40,430
I have to pay for the medicine every month.

349
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:43,230
If not so,

350
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,780
with your more than ten years of experience as a senior worker,

351
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:47,670
I'd really hate to let you go.

352
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,940
Then why do you fire me?

353
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:54,090
You are driving our family

354
00:18:54,090 --> 00:18:54,980
to the wall now.

355
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:56,890
How could you say that?

356
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:58,890
I'm not driving you to the wall.

357
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:02,690
It seems that they haven't called you yet.

358
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:06,660
Who?

359
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:09,720
You really didn't receive their message.

360
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:11,640
Alright, I'll give them a call now.

361
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:14,500
Come in please.

362
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,940
Finally you're here. Have a seat.

363
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,750
I was about to call you,

364
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,150
No need to call me.

365
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:24,360
I'm here.

366
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:27,110
Who is this?

367
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:28,510
This is Bai.

368
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,100
This is the one you are looking for.

369
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:32,720
Mr. Bai, nice to meet you.

370
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,940
Sorry. My hands are dirty.

371
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:40,160
Bai, this is

372
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:43,560
the HR manager of Tong Jie Refrigeration Equipment Company.

373
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:44,400
His name is Miao.

374
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:47,060
You can call him Manager Miao from now on.

375
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:52,070
Then you two have a chat first.

376
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:54,520
I have some business to do.

377
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:55,830
Please help yourself.

378
00:19:55,850 --> 00:19:56,530
OK. OK.

379
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:01,780
Mr. Bai, here is the thing,

380
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:04,280
our company wants to hire you

381
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:07,030
as the engineer in our technology department.

382
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:09,590
Your take-home pay will be 20,000 yuan per month.

383
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:10,960
Every month,

384
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:12,520
we will provide you a travel allowance.

385
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:15,380
And 5,000 yuan of housing subsidy.

386
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:19,010
Meal allowance, and transportation allowance, each amounting to 2,000 yuan.

387
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,400
You work eight hours a day,

388
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:23,000
and enjoy weekends and holidays off...

389
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:23,880
Manager Miao,

390
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:28,340
does your company print counterfeit money?

391
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:33,910
Mr. Bai, you are so humorous.

392
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:35,810
I'm not being humorous.

393
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:38,610
The conditions your company offers are so unreliable.

394
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:40,290
Mr. Bai,

395
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:45,400
Mr. Bai, this is my business card.

396
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:46,320
Please take it.

397
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:51,930
I guess you've worked here for over a decade.

398
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,660
You probably know

399
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:55,120
the business of this factory.

400
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:57,800
Half of the components used in our company

401
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,600
were produced by your factory.

402
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:02,460
And I also know your factory manager.

403
00:21:02,630 --> 00:21:03,850
You can trust me.

404
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:07,970
The point is I know nothing about the technology.

405
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:10,060
Don't worry.

406
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:12,230
We'll arrange someone to guide you.

407
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:13,980
If so,

408
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,500
you can directly hire a real engineer.

409
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:18,140
That would be more convenient.

410
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:19,030
Mr. Bai,

411
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,940
